\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Staff Aspects\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The controls in the lower portion of the System Inspector relate to the staves of the inspected system.  There is a column of Staff Buttons, which select the staff or staves to be inspected.  This is a scrolling column of buttons, in case there are more staves than can be accommodated in the visible portion of the column, as shown in this example, where the system contains 19 staves:\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qc\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_11.tiff \width4260\height3080
}¬} \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 To aid identification of the staves, each staff button is numbered with the staff number, and a miniature icon relating to the staff and clef (if any) is displayed on the button. Multiple staves can be selected by Shift-clicking or drag-selecting the staff buttons.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The staff aspects are as follows.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Standard\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 An example of this aspect is shown above.  In this aspect the usual attributes of staves are specified.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 N\f1 umber of lines\f0 : the number of lines in the selected staff or staves.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 taff Hidden\f0 : if the box is checked, the selected staff or staves will not appear.  Hidden staves do not take part in adjustment (see \b Adjustment\b0 ), so the effect of hidden staves on adjustment will not be noticed on visible staves.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 N\f1 otation type\f0 :  Specifies the type of notation that is expected to appear on the selected staff or staves.  The notation type has an effect on the size and formatting of the material on the staff.  The buttons are (left-to-right): Staff, Tablature, Chant.  The default option is Staff.  Chant is chosen for Gregorian chant staves (containing Solesmes-style neumes).  The spacing between lines of a chant staff is 50% wider than that of the standard staff to accommodate neumes.  Tablature is chosen for lute tablature staves. The spacing between lines of a tablature staff is 50% wider than that of the standard staff to accommodate tablature symbols.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ize\f0 :  chooses the size of the selected staff or staves relative to the standard size specified in the Document Preferences.  This is used only for setting cue staves or ossia within a system, and \i should not be used\i0  in place of a Rastral number (see \b Document Preferences\b0 ) to set the size of a system.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 P\f1 art name\f0 :  A popup menu listing all the currently defined part names (see \b Parts\b0 ).  Changing the part name associated with a staff by selecting with the Part name popup takes effect immediately on the selected staff or staves, so it is not necessary to press \fs24\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ET\f0 .\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 \par
