\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 P\f1 reface\f0 : if the box is checked, the left indentation area will be used as an preface (or incipit) for the selected staff or staves.  The indentation area will be filled with a prefatory staff.  The \fs24\f1\b0\i0 L\f1 eft\f0  and \fs24\f1\b0\i0 R\f1 ight\f0  fields specify the extent filled by the prefatory staff, where the left end of the indentation area counts as 0% and the right end counts as 100%.  The default values are Left=0% and Right=100%,  as shown in the 3-staff example at the beginning of this section.  For example, making the Left End greater than 0% permits space for a title, and making a Right End less than 100% allows a gap between the prefatory staff and the main staff.  It is necessary to specify a left indent using the system Indentation aspect described above.  If there is no indentation area, Preface has no effect.\par
