\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\fs24\f1\b0\i0 T\f1 op Margin\f0 :  Specifies an amount of vertical space above the selected staff or staves.  This amount is a "guaranteed minimum".  The usual purpose of this is to make allowance for extra text or punctuation above the staff.  It is not necessary to make manual allowance for notes placed high on the staff and for bar numbers and staff headers, as this allowance is made automatically.  The units (ss) are "staff spaces" (the vertical height of space between staff lines).  A default value is supplied.  Setting \fs24\f1\b0\i0 F\f1 ixed\f0  \i limits\i0  the Top Margin to the value indicated, regardless of the contents of the staff.\par
